<paragraph blockId="15.[133,1154,1222,1676]" lastBlockId="16.[133,1154,226,373]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">
Male. (with damaged head and hypopygium). Frons brown, clearly broader than long, with 60–70 hairs and dense but very fine microtrichia. SAs robust but lower pair shorter. The antials lower on frons than anterolaterals, and about as far from upper SAs as either is from an AL bristle. Pre-ocellars further apart than upper SAs but about equidistant from each other and as either is from a mediolateral bristle, which is about the same level on frons. Cheek with 5 bristles and jowl with a longer one. Postpedicels with SPS vesicles (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1140,1376,1400]" captionStart="Figs 61–64" captionStartId="14.[133,170,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,760,1601]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 61–64. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 61 – postpedicels (ruptured), palps a proboscis; 62 – labellum from below; 63 – notopleuron with cleft; 64 – right side of scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252187/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[401,484,1406,1430]" captionStart="Figs 61–64" captionStartId="14.[133,170,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,760,1601]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 61–64. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 61 – postpedicels (ruptured), palps a proboscis; 62 – labellum from below; 63 – notopleuron with cleft; 64 – right side of scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252187/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
, with the lower faces of labella as 
<figureCitation box="[891,974,1406,1430]" captionStart="Figs 61–64" captionStartId="14.[133,170,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,760,1601]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 61–64. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 61 – postpedicels (ruptured), palps a proboscis; 62 – labellum from below; 63 – notopleuron with cleft; 64 – right side of scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252187/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
. Thorax brown. Two notopleural bristles and a cleft in front of these (
<figureCitation box="[736,820,1437,1461]" captionStart="Figs 61–64" captionStartId="14.[133,170,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,760,1601]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 61–64. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 61 – postpedicels (ruptured), palps a proboscis; 62 – labellum from below; 63 – notopleuron with cleft; 64 – right side of scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252187/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron bare (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1139,1437,1461]" captionStart="Figs 61–64" captionStartId="14.[133,170,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,760,1601]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 61–64. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 61 – postpedicels (ruptured), palps a proboscis; 62 – labellum from below; 63 – notopleuron with cleft; 64 – right side of scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252187/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of hairs and a posterior pair of bristles (
<figureCitation box="[928,1011,1468,1492]" captionStart="Figs 61–64" captionStartId="14.[133,170,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[137,1153,760,1601]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 61–64. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 61 – postpedicels (ruptured), palps a proboscis; 62 – labellum from below; 63 – notopleuron with cleft; 64 – right side of scutellum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252187/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites brown with numerous hairs that are longest at the rear of T6. Venter brown, and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[603,733,1529,1553]" captionStart="Figs 65–70" captionStartId="15.[133,170,1172,1191]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1143]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 65–70. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 65–67 – hypopygium; 68 – front tarsus; 69 – hind femur; 70 –wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252189/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Figs 65–67</figureCitation>
. Legs brown but parts of front legs yellowish brown or paler. Fore tarsus as 
<figureCitation box="[597,681,1560,1584]" captionStart="Figs 65–70" captionStartId="15.[133,170,1172,1191]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1143]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 65–70. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 65–67 – hypopygium; 68 – front tarsus; 69 – hind femur; 70 –wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252189/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.8 times its length. Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[634,721,1590,1614]" captionStart="Figs 65–70" captionStartId="15.[133,170,1172,1191]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1143]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 65–70. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 65–67 – hypopygium; 68 – front tarsus; 69 – hind femur; 70 –wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252189/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with a dozen moderately differentiated posterodorsal hairs and a longer pre-apical, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[492,574,1652,1676]" captionStart="Figs 65–70" captionStartId="15.[133,170,1172,1191]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1143]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 65–70. Megaselia turkuensis n. sp. male: 65–67 – hypopygium; 68 – front tarsus; 69 – hind femur; 70 –wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252189/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="26">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[590,674,1652,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="15" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.44. Costal ratios 3.4: 2.0–2.1: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[569,668,226,250]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
long. Hair at base of vein 3 small. With 3 axillary bristles, the outer being 
<quantity box="[488,584,256,280]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
